                        <interp inst="t18391021-name-355" type="surname" value="CORNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391021-name-355" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CORNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an apprentice to Thomas Vesper and another, pawnbrokers, in Sydney-place, Commercial-road. On Saturday night, the 28th of September, at half-past six o'clock, I was outside the shop, and saw the prisoner take this coat from the rail outside—I ran after him, and secured him before he got one hundred yards—he threw it down by our back gate—it was taken up by one of our lads—this is it.</p>
